class="block-intro-text"><p>Color plays an important role in branding, as it has both a psychological and physical effect on viewers. While no color is inherently bad, each can influence perceptions among customers about the nature of your business. Our guide highlights the most common perceptions attached to popular colors used in logos to make the design process easier.</p></div></div></div></div><div
class="section-content"><div
class="container"><div
class="narrow-container"><div
class="block-global-cta button-cta"><div
class="cta-wrapper without-image"><div
class="cta-info"><p
class="cta-heading">Launch your business with a free logo</p>
<a
href="https://www.notzarla.com/free-logo-maker?utm_source=zarla&amp;utm_medium=internal&amp;utm_campaign=zd-guideslogos-buttonintrotextbelow&amp;utm_term=en-startdesigningacustomlogo-20240613" class="btn btn-primary">Start designing a custom logo</a><ul
class="features"><li><p><strong>Trustpilot: Rated Excellent</strong> with 3,918 reviews</p></li><li><p><strong>Over 500k+ logos have been created with Zarla</strong></p></li></ul></div></div></div><div
class="block"><h2 id=logo-colors-and-meanings>Logo Colors and Meanings:</h2><h3 id=1-red>1. Red.</h3><p>Red signifies strength, determination, and power. Using red in your logo tells customers that your business is a force to be reckoned with, or that you have confidence in your goods and brand. Red is also associated with love and erotic feelings, making this a good color to use for a product or service related to these emotions.</p><p>Red is considered an effective color to use when calling customers to action. As such, it is often used in advertising for high-energy concepts such as sports and fast cars.</p></div><div
class="block block-image-gallery"><div
class="image-gallery"><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Coca-Cola-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Coca Cola brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Nintendo-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Nintendo brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Target-Zarla-2400x2401-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Target brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/CNN-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="CNN brand logo."></div></div></div><div
class="block"><h3 id=2-orange>2. Orange.</h3><p>Orange inspires feelings of motivation, positivity, and enthusiasm. It is a warm color without the intensity of a color like red. Orange has been shown to stimulate mental activity, and as such, is used by brands that are creative and playful.</p><p>Orange is generally well-received by younger people. It is also often associated with healthy food and citrus, making it an excellent color to use for a food brand.</p></div><div
class="block block-image-gallery"><div
class="image-gallery"><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Nickelodeon-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Nickelodeon brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/The-Home-Depot-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="The Home Depot brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/SoundCloud-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="SoundCloud brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Blogger-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Blogger brand logo."></div></div></div><div
class="block"><h3 id=3-yellow>3. Yellow.</h3><p>Yellow is widely considered the color of happiness and positivity, as it is associated with the sun. Similar to orange, yellow inspires mental activity and stimulates the brain. The color stands out well against darker backgrounds and generally grabs attention.</p><p>Men tend to view yellow as a childish color, so it would be ill-advised to use yellow for masculine, upscale products. The color would work well for products aimed at children, however.</p></div><div
class="block block-image-gallery"><div
class="image-gallery"><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/McDonalds-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="McDonald&#039;s brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/DHL-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="DHL brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Sprint-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Sprint brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Best-Buy-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Best Buy brand logo."></div></div></div><div
class="block"><h3 id=4-green>4. Green.</h3><p>Green is often associated with nature and healthy food, as thriving plants are usually green. As such, this is an excellent color to use when promoting eco-friendly, organic, or health-focused products.</p><p>Green is very comfortable on the human eye, making it somewhat relaxing to look at. As such, green can be used to indicate safety. Darker shades of green are linked to money and success, making it a great choice when conveying a company's status.</p></div><div
class="block block-image-gallery"><div
class="image-gallery"><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Tropicana-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Tropicana brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/British-petroleum-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="British Petroleum brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Holiday-Inn-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Holiday Inn brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Whatsapp-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Whatsapp brand logo."></div></div></div><div
class="block"><h3 id=5-blue>5. Blue.</h3><p>Blue is a cool and relaxing color, making viewers feel at ease. The color is known to inspire feelings of trust. Blue has also been used to convey wisdom, trust, and confidence. Because blue is the same color as the ocean and sky, this color is perfect to use for brands related to flight, water, or sailing.</p><p>Blue is often considered a masculine color and is used for products aimed at men. Dark blue is perceived as a serious color, and does well for logos related to technology and intelligence.</p></div><div
class="block block-image-gallery"><div
class="image-gallery"><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/GE-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="General Electric brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Oral-B-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Oral-B brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Oreo-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Oreo brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Facebook-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Facebook brand logo."></div></div></div><div
class="block"><h3 id=6-purple>6. Purple.</h3><p>Purple has proven incredibly popular among children and is commonly associated with creativity, mystery, and magic. Historically, purple was known as the color of royalty, and some shades can convey nobility, dignity, and luxury.</p><p>Because of its composition, purple has some of the romantic connotations of red but with a calmer undertone, thanks to blue influences. Light purple has worked well for products aimed at women.</p></div><div
class="block block-image-gallery"><div
class="image-gallery"><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Cadbury-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Cadbury brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/SyFy-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="SyFy brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Fedex-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="FedEx brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Yahoo-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Yahoo! brand logo."></div></div></div><div
class="block"><h3 id=7-black>7. Black.</h3><p>Black is considered a serious, formal, and classy color. It is associated with formality and structure. There are some negative connotations to black, predominantly related to death and the unknown.</p><p>As a background color, black allows many other colors to pop. When paired with other "serious" colors such as red or orange, your logo will have an air of authority and power.</p></div><div
class="block block-image-gallery"><div
class="image-gallery"><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Adidas-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Adidas brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Playstation-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="PlayStation brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Louis-vuitton-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Louis Vuitton brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Apple-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Apple brand logo."></div></div></div><div
class="block"><h3 id=8-white>8. White.</h3><p>White is an overwhelmingly positive color, with links to purity, cleanliness, peace, and innocence. It works well for brands related to health care, thanks to its association with sterility. White is also considered a simple color without flaws.</p><p>Because clouds are white, many people think of white as being heavenly. It is also the color of milk, and would do well for a dairy product logo.</p></div><div
class="block block-image-gallery"><div
class="image-gallery"><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Mercedes-benz-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Mercedez Benz brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Toyota-logo-Zarla-1024x1024-20210830.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Toyota brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Renault-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Logotipo de la marca Renault"></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Peugeot-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Peugeot brand logo."></div></div></div><div
class="block"><h3 id=9-brown>9. Brown.</h3><p>Arguably the most common association with brown is chocolate. A close competitor is coffee, making this the perfect color for a logo for either product. Brown is a warm color and is linked to feelings of comfort and stability.</p><p>Brown is a common color in nature, making it a great choice for natural or earthy products. Soil is brown, so a brand that sells produce or plants may benefit from using brown in its logo.</p></div><div
class="block block-image-gallery"><div
class="image-gallery"><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/UPS-logo-Zarla-2155x2155-20210830.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="UPS brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Hard-Rock-Cafe-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Hard Rock Cafe brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/MM-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="M&amp;M brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Coffee-house-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Coffee House brand logo."></div></div></div><div
class="block"><h3 id=10-pink>10. Pink.</h3><p>Pink is commonly considered a feminine color with links to youth, romance, and calmness. The color is often associated with elegance and sophistication. Lighter shades of pink can come across as childish.</p><p>Deeper shades of pink are linked more strongly to red, sharing connotations of love and seduction. Dusty pink is considered a more mature shade than pastels. Bright pink often conveys energy, fun, and excitement.</p></div><div
class="block block-image-gallery"><div
class="image-gallery"><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Barbie-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Barbie brand logo."></div><div
class="image">
<img
data-src="https://www.notzarla.com/images/Victoria-Secret-Zarla-2400x2400-20210818.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=150&dpr=2" class="lazyload" alt="Pink Victoria Secret brand logo."></div><div
